{# portfolio -- a DESIGN SPECIMEN, not an application document.

   For a personal site or folio, where the design IS the work sample and no parser
   will ever read it. Layout constraints are relaxed here BECAUSE the reader is
   always human. Honesty and contrast constraints are not relaxed, because those
   protect the reader, not the parser.

   Renders from the SAME resume.yaml as the Apply track. That is the whole point:
   fact parity is structural rather than something a human has to diff. If the two
   documents ever disagree, the source is wrong and both are wrong together.

   Ships a mandatory footer marking it as a specimen, so it can never be mistaken
   for the document you'd actually submit.

   Do NOT send this to an employer. Use `signature` (or a preset) for that. #}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block page_extra %}
@page :first { margin-top: 0; }
{% endblock %}

{% block style %}
:root {
  --font-body: var(--font-sans);
  --font-head: var(--font-sans);
  --spec: {{ config.band | default(accent, true) | default('#12313C', true) }};
  --page-margin-y: 0.75in;
  --page-margin-x: 0.85in;
  --lh-body: 1.5;
}

/* Display masthead, full-bleed. Same correction as signature: no negative margins,
   @page side margins are 0, @page :first drops the top margin. */
.masthead {
  background: var(--spec);
  color: #fff;
  padding: calc(var(--page-margin-y) + 14pt) var(--page-margin-x) 34pt;
  margin: 0 0 var(--sp-8);
}
.name {
  font-size: 46pt;
  font-weight: var(--w-bold);
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  line-height: 0.98;
  color: #fff;
  max-width: 8em;
}
.headline {
  font-size: 13pt;
  font-weight: var(--w-medium);
  margin-top: var(--sp-4);
  padding-top: var(--sp-4);
  border-top: 1.5pt solid rgba(255,255,255,.28);
  color: #E4EDF1;              /* measured >=4.5:1 on every shipped band */
  max-width: 26em;
}
.contact { margin-top: var(--sp-4); font-size: var(--fs-meta); color: #E4EDF1; }
.contact span + span::before { content: "/"; margin: 0 8pt; color: rgba(255,255,255,.45); }

/* Headings as a numbered editorial index.
   MEASURED: a CSS counter DOES appear in the extracted text ("01 SUMMARY"), because
   Chrome renders generated content as real glyphs. Harmless here -- this document is
   never parsed, that is the whole premise of the portfolio track -- but it is why the
   fact-parity check must compare FACTS (employers, dates, metrics) rather than every
   numeric token: the folio's stream legitimately contains 01-04 and the Apply track's
   does not. Do not copy this idiom onto the Apply track. */
body { counter-reset: sec; }
h2 {
  counter-increment: sec;
  border: none;
  padding: 0 0 var(--sp-2) 0;
  font-size: 9pt;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  color: var(--spec);
  border-bottom: 1.5pt solid var(--spec);
}
h2::before {
  content: counter(sec, decimal-leading-zero);
  margin-right: 9pt;
  opacity: .45;
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
}
h2::after { content: none; }

section { margin-top: var(--sp-8); }
.role { font-size: 13pt; }
.org, .orgline { color: var(--spec); font-weight: var(--w-medium); }
.subrow { margin-top: 0; }
.entry { margin-top: var(--sp-5); }
.entry-summary { margin-top: var(--sp-2); }
.line { margin-top: var(--sp-2); }
.summary .prose { font-size: 13pt; line-height: 1.45; max-width: 30em; color: var(--c-ink); }

/* The one place a real two-column grid is allowed in this repo: no parser will
   ever read this file, and the Apply track carries the same facts in one column. */
.skills { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-6); }
.skill-row { display: block; break-inside: avoid; }
.skill-row dt {
  font-size: 8.5pt; font-weight: var(--w-bold); letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--c-muted); margin-bottom: 2pt;
}
.skill-row dd { font-size: 10.5pt; }

li::before { content: "—"; color: var(--spec); opacity: .5; }
li { padding-left: 15pt; }

.specimen {
  margin-top: var(--sp-8);
  padding-top: var(--sp-3);
  border-top: var(--rule-hair) solid var(--c-rule);
  font-size: 8.5pt;
  color: var(--c-muted);      /* 7.1:1 -- a disclosure nobody can read is not one */
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}
{% endblock %}

{% block footer %}
{# Mandatory. This document must never be mistaken for the application copy. #}
<div class="specimen">Design specimen — application copy available on request.</div>
{% endblock %}
